Scope:
  Exact integer arithmetic checks the cross determinant

    Lambda(TR_(j+1))Lambda(R_j)-Lambda(R_(j+1))Lambda(TR_j)

  for all displayed ranks, endpoint powers, and `1<=j<=6`.  The 7,182
  target cases are exactly `j=2`, `r>=2`, and `M-r>=2`; all pass.  The
  second run finds no negative `j=2` minor anywhere in its larger box,
  even outside the target cone.  The
  reported negative higher-index minors and alternating-sign failures show
  that neither unrestricted connection-minor positivity nor a naive
  checkerboard-sign theorem explains the result.  The target checks remain
  bounded evidence for the cyclic-alias range.
